Class ExecutionResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.smartthings.sdk.smartapp.core.models.ExecutionResponse

  • @Generated(value="io.swagger.codegen.languages.JavaClientCodegen",

public class ExecutionResponse
extends java.lang.Object
    Expected response structure for an SmartApp execution. An execution response is compositional in nature. Client's should set exactly one *Data field depending on the type of execution. For example, if the execution request's lifecycle was of type EVENT, the \"eventData\" field should be returned.
